Ah, I see what you mean now. You're referring to the text box that appears when you click the "Choose File" button on the file input field. This text box usually displays the name of the file you've selected. 

To ensure this text box displays properly, you need to ensure that the `id` attribute of your file input element matches the selector used in your JavaScript code. Here's how you can set up your HTML file input element:

```html
<input type="file" id="fileInput" accept=".json">
```

This HTML input element creates a file input field with the id "fileInput" and accepts only JSON files (.json) for upload.

The text box should now appear when you click the "Choose File" button, and it will display the name of the selected file after you've chosen one. This behavior is handled automatically by the browser, so you don't need to write any additional JavaScript code for it.